            All has been said about this game from the footballing side, and I agree. However I think Szymon Marciniak deserves credit. I'm the first to slate referees when they have terrible performances or bottle big decisions against big teams, at intimidating stadiums etc but today he was excellent. Completely resisted the Barcelona tactic of 'fall over dramatically and look to the ref' in the hope that is enough to buy you a free kick regardless of whether it is a foul or not. It works with Spanish referees at the Nou Camp (and most away matches in the champions league too). He also ignored the same tactic used by a number of PSG players. Without looking at every incident in slow motion, I would guess he got 95% of the decisions correct. I don't know much about him, how high his general standard of officiating is but he was great tonight. Not perfect, but fans would accept this consistency every week- especially those of us who are fans of premier league teams.
